(Corrects percentage gain in headline and first paragraph.
The story was initially published yesterday.)  African tea prices surged 3.3
percent to an average of $2.77 a kilogram at a weekly sale in
 Mombasa ,  Kenya , Tea Brokers East Africa Ltd. said in an e-mailed
statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
